{
  "title": "TextOptions",
  "description": "Construction options for a Text node — a flat merge of visual TextStyleOptions (appearance) and LayoutOptions (flow / overflow), plus two construction-only flags. The two source interfaces share no keys, so the flat shape is unambiguous. ```ts const label = new Text('Hello', { fillColor, fontSize: 24, maxWidth: 360 }); ```",
  "symbol": "TextOptions",
  "kind": "interface",
  "subsystem": "rendering",
